mmunications skills\u2014able to communicate and drive clarity in cross-team discussions. Exceptional ability to track many moving details and followup accordingly. Exceptional writing skills. Exceptional project management skills. Bonus points if you have: Prior experience managing projects. Prior experience working in politics, activism, or online organizing. A passion for helping Americans access and exercise their right to vote. Some of the benefits of working here: Outspoken, queer, female founder and CEO Short commute. We all work from home and it is just the best. Parent friendly policies. If you need to take 3-5pm off every day to get your kids from school and make after school snacks, we\u2019re totally cool with that. Generous time off. Unlimited paid vacation with leadership approval. Highly competent, down to earth, and humble team. Awesome slack channels. #pets, #politics, #memes and #random are our favs. How to apply: You\u2019ll need a resume and the ability to answer a handful of short questions. We don\u2019t require a cover letter, because you don\u2019t want to write one and we don\u2019t want to read one. Applications are processed on a rolling basis, and we will accept applications until the role is filled. We are, however, looking to fill this role ASAP, so you should apply as soon as you can. VoteAmerica is an equal opportunity employer. This means that we don\u2019t discriminate against people because of their race, ethnicity, sex, age, religion, national origin, marital status, pregnancy, personal appearance, veteran status, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, family responsibilities, matriculation, genetic information, or political affiliation. We cannot provide sponsorship for those requiring visas or work permits. If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of the\u00c2\u00a0requirements, apply anyway! More Jobs Website Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design